    <abstract>
        <para>
            &octave-app; is the <trademark class =
            "registered">Matlab</trademark>-clone which comes closest to the
            original.  Though it tries to be fully compatible, it features its
            own extensions and improvements over the functionality of the
            commercial <trademark class = "registered">Matlab</trademark>
            product.
        </para>

        <para>
            &octave-app; is shipped with a 340+ page reference manual, which
            also tries to be a bit of a user guide.  Despite its size the
            documentation is incomplete, and where it stops, &coda; starts:
            &coda-long; approaches &octave-app; purely from the user's point of
            view, explaining e.g. <filename>oct</filename>-file construction in
            a tutorial like form.
        </para>
    </abstract>
